    <div class="rightSection" id="preshipment">
        <p1>
            <h2>Pre-Shipment</h2>
            <br>All consoles must be shipped out inside of a clear plastic bag, as well as a foam bag. When you have completed verification, package the console accordingly. It is the verifier's responsibility to include a yellow "HAC Notice" before sending
            the package to the warehouse for shipping.
            <br>Once the console has been packaged appropriately, a HAC Notice is included, and verification is complete for ALL ROs, the order is fully complete and ready to be placed with outgoing work.
        </p1>
    </div>
    <div class="rightSection" id="Discrepancies">
        <p1>
            <h2>Discrepancies/Failures</h2>
            If you encounter a "Manager Approval" message during Verification, this is an indicator of one of two scenarios. Either:
            <li>You have made a mistake in your entry,</li>
            or
            <li>You have correctly entered the information, but it does not match what the database expects.</li>

            <br>If you are certain that you have made a mistake in entry, such as accidentally clicking a Blue JoyCon when you have a Gray, it is acceptable to start over from the beginning and enter the correct information.
            <div style="color:red"><b> If you have entered the information correctly as you have the item in front of you and the failure is occurring anyway, this RO <b><u>MUST</u></b> be processed as a discrepancy.</b>
            </div>
            <div style="color:red"><b>Never assume that you know what is wrong with the RO, and never use "the process of elimination" to get through the form. It is imperative to remember that your role is to fail things in verification if need be, not pass them in spite of the issues. Failing to do this is to blatantly disregard our quality standards, and is likely to cause a serious consumer-facing problem, for which you would be directly responsible.</b></div>
            <br>If you encounter a true failure/discrepancy, write down the step of the form that you last entered before the RO displayed the "Manager Approval" message on a piece of masking tape and affix it to the top of the box. Please also write
            down the RO number you were processing, as there may be several ROs in the box. Place the discrepancy in the designated location, do NOT place it with your outgoing completed work.
        </p1>
    </div>
